window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>At the heart of this tragic history is one of Shakespeare's most noble characters, the statesman Brutus, who is caught in a devastating conflict between private affection and public duty. </p> <p>Julius Caesar has become the most powerful man in the Rome. Does his power now threaten the very existence of the Republic itself? A conspiracy is hatched, one that will have fatal consequences not only for Caesar and the conspirators but for the future history of the ancient world. </p> <p>Brutus is played by John Bowe and Mark Antony by Adrian Lester. Michael Feast is Caesar.</p>"; 
